    Ummm, you appear to have missed the entire gist of this discussion.  This discussion is trying to determine what cannot be determined, and that is: Do stat buffs affect pets?<br>
<br>
   You may not believe this, but my observations are as valid as anyones for one simple fact:  We cannot see our pets/warders stats, therefore we can neither prove, nor disprove the value of giving stats buffs to pets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You are seeing things.<br>
Here is a hint: go to option and turn NPC spell on.<br>
You will see air/water casts.<br>
Only pet that procs inately is Epic.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   Basing the assumption on this means that every melee out there with proc weapons, plus about 80+% of all mobs in the game cast instead of proc.   When a Rogue is wielding a proc'ing weapons, say a Stilleto Of Bloodclaw, you will see the message 'soandso begins to cast a spell', further when fighting LDC's, I often see them casting boil blood, but I know they proc due to the fact that their melee is not interrupted by the proc.<br>
<br>
   My reason for suspecting this to be the case is based on Cyricus' parsings.   If you look closely, you will see that the Epic and Earth pets have a higher combat delay than the Air and Water.<br>
<br>
  Further examination will show that the Air and Water have the same combat delay as the Skele and wolf pets, as well as the Beastlord warder at one time, none of which have an innate proc/cast issue.<br>
<br>
   Additionally, if you watch very closely, you will notice that the Air and Water pets do not cast until they are engaged in melee, whereas the Earth and Epic will cast at range occasionally.<br>
<br>
   Finally, if you watch the Air/Water pet closely, as well as the combat spam, you will see that the Air/Water pet swing immediately preceeding the 'soandso begins to cast a spell' message, whereas with the Earth pet, there is often a delay between swings and the message.<br>
<br>
   So based on this, while it is possible that they do cat instead of proc, it is more likely that they proc instead.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Just because BL sta buff sucks doesn't mean sta is not important.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   I am not saying that, instead I am pointing out that saying pets do not gain from STA buffs, cannot be proven or disproven based on the tools we currently have available to us as players.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>By chance does anyone know if this is a thread just stating facts about pets or are we suggesting changes?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
